[As an epidemiologist, I would point out that when the Pope visited
Zambia some years ago, a large number of Catholic clergy came in from
the bush to participate in the various activities. One arrived at the
local seminary not having eaten all his pork sandwiches or sausages
(the details evade me). These were thrown out and got fed to the pigs
kept in pens behind the buildings. They promptly came down with ASF.
This was told me by my one-time graduate student, Dr Kenny Samui, now
Dean of the veterinary school in Lusaka, so I know it to be so. -
Mod.MHJ
